  "body": "The section_item has become pretty big because it contains all the community properties that are needed for the community profile popup and community section.\r\n\r\nWe need to create a community store and when opening the popup, we populate that store from the service using the community Id so that we don't have to put it all in section_item.\r\n\r\nHere it is explained by Sale:\r\nThat popup which is opened on \"EditCommunity\", should work with the  \"CommunityStore\" for example\r\non an action when we need to open that popup we just need to pass id of the community\r\nthat popup updates \"CommunityStore\" finding appropriate chat section store (for that community) and setting it to the property \"communitySectionModule\"\r\nstore will look something like this:\r\n\r\n```qml\r\nQtObject {\r\n    id: root\r\n\r\n    property string communityId: \"\"\r\n    property var chatCommunitySectionModule\r\n\r\n    onCommunityIdChanged: {\r\n        mainModule.prepareCommunitySectionModuleForCommunityId(root.communityId)\r\n        root.chatCommunitySectionModule = mainModule.getCommunitySectionModule()\r\n    }\r\n\r\n    // This is just a dummy example what functions we should have there\r\n    function getCommunityName(){\r\n        if(!root.chatCommunitySectionModule)\r\n            return \"\"\r\n        return root.chatCommunitySectionModule.getCommunityName()\r\n    }\r\n ```\r\n that means every time we open that popup we just set communityId of the store and related components knows to display everything needed from that store",
